title: PPPP’s Qazi Ahmed Saeed wins PP-256 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 10 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP), Qazi Ahmed Saeed has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-256, Rahim Yar Khan-II by securing 28,466 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Muhammad Amir Nawaz Khan, an independent candidate who bagged 23,921 votes.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 47.25 percent.
